Sentences are withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.  Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Have no association with any known drug users or dealers;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
6) Pay costs of action;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) On the drug paraphernalia conviction: Total Ten (10) days jail; Two (2) days up front, under the Huber Law, to commence on 11-15-14 at 8:00 a.m.  Eight (8) days jail, stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion.  
9) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process. 
$150.00 cash bail applied to court costs. 
Letter from defendant's fiance.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
